%N A128885 Number of closed orientable irreducible 3-manifolds of complexity n.
%D A128885 S. Matveev, Algorithmic Topology and Classification of 3-Manifolds, Springer, 2003.
%H A128885 Bruno Martelli, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/math/0405250">Complexity of 3-manifolds</a>, arXiv:math/0405250 [math.GT], 2004-2005.
%H A128885 S. Matveev, <a href="http://www.matlas.math.csu.ru">Atlas of 3-manifolds</a>. The data for n = 12 may be incomplete, showing only 23434 manifolds.
%H A128885 S. V. Matveev and V. V. Tarkaev, <a href="https://www.mathnet.ru/eng/cheb910">Recognition and tabulation of 3-manifolds up to complexity 13</a>, Chebyshevskii Sbornik, 21 (2020), 290-300.
%H A128885 A. Yu. Vesnin, S. V. Matveev, and E. A. Fominykh, <a href="https://www.mathnet.ru/eng/semr331">Complexity of 3-dimensional manifolds: exact values and estimates</a>, Siberian Electronic Mathematical Reports, 8 (2011), 341-364 [in Russian]. Theorem 2.1 gives erroneous a(12) = 23452.
%Y A128885 A005418 seems to enumerate lens spaces by complexity, see Martelli.
